{
  "stem": "985.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to reregister that we are-- some of them registered as Greek, as Czech-- anything but-- so we was going to-- to be with-- We want to go to our homeland, which, obviously, in order to go to Greece from Poland, you have to go west and south, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they let us out, the Russians.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they didn't care so much. the Polish they just-- they didn't care.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So finally we wound up in Linz, which is northern-- all through Germany, it was a whole odyssey.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We-- we hitched-- hitchhiked trains and-- and with people, and we stayed over in farmhouses, and they fed us and gave us food, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we wound up in-- in Linz, which is the northern part of Austria.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And subsequently we had to go through Salzburg.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Salzburg is on the border of Austria and Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It's about, like, four miles from this-- from the heart of the town-- from-- from-- from downtown Salzburg to the German border.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we were supposed to stay there the night, the next day go to-- to Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was a camp-- a big Jewish camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And from there, there were transports going to Israel, and somebody want to stay in Germany, at DP camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- I went to-- to Salzburg.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I stayed overnight.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the next day was a beautiful day, so I figured, ah, let me stay another day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why not?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I stayed for four years, there, really, because I liked the town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I never went anywhere else.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What was the name of that DP camp?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, there were-- which one, in Salzburg?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were a few.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't stay there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I stayed only a few days.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was Parsch, P-A-R-S-C-H, was one.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
